This paper proposes a method for reconstructing and labeling a 3D scene from a single depth image using adversarial learning. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) tasks such as semantic scene completion and uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly found in the computer science sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of robotics (RO) and the effectiveness of the model's internal representation, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses a variational auto-encoder to reconstruct the complete semantic scene, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR).
